../codex_findings.md:56:`withdrawToNativeChain()` also accepts `zrc20 == _ETH_ADDRESS_` without requiring real ETH funding. In that branch, no asset is transferred in, but the function still proceeds with an attacker-chosen `amount` and can drive swaps/withdrawals against tokens already held by the contract.
../codex_findings.md:62:Make `withdraw()` internal or access-controlled, and require `msg.value == amount` for ETH input flows in `withdrawToNativeChain()`.
../codex_findings.md:116:### 5. `GatewaySend.depositAndCall()` does not bind source-side swap input/output assets
../codex_findings.md:121:- `GatewaySend`
../codex_findings.md:124:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:195`
../codex_findings.md:125:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:218`
../codex_findings.md:126:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:239`
../codex_findings.md:127:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:245`
../codex_findings.md:128:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:258`
../codex_findings.md:138:As a result, a caller can supply one visible input while instructing DODO and the gateway logic to consume or bridge a different asset already held by `GatewaySend`.
../codex_findings.md:141:Residual ETH or ERC20 balances inside `GatewaySend` can be swapped and bridged out by arbitrary users.
../codex_findings.md:146:### 6. `GatewaySend.onCall()` has an ABI-incompatible return type and cannot receive authenticated calls
../codex_findings.md:151:- `GatewaySend`
../codex_findings.md:154:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:341`
../codex_findings.md:155:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:344`
../codex_findings.md:160:`GatewaySend.onCall()` is declared as `returns (bytes4)`, but Zeta's `Callable` interface requires `returns (bytes memory)`. `GatewayEVM` performs a typed external call and ABI-decodes the returndata as dynamic bytes. Returning fixed-size `bytes4` breaks that decode step.
../codex_findings.md:163:Authenticated destination-side calls into `GatewaySend` revert at the gateway boundary even if the callee body itself executed correctly.
../codex_findings.md:170:### 7. `GatewaySend` source-side ETH accounting can overcharge users
../codex_findings.md:175:- `GatewaySend`
../codex_findings.md:178:- `contracts/GatewaySend.sol:195`
